---
import { vsAgency } from "../site";
import SectionIntro from "./SectionIntro.astro";
---

<section class="section vs-agency-section" aria-label="WSS versus agency comparison">
  <div class="shell">
    <SectionIntro
      eyebrow="Why not an agency?"
      title="Agencies execute tactics. We build systems."
      body="Both have a place. The difference matters most when the constraint is decision-making, not delivery."
    />

    <div class="vs-table-wrap">
      <table class="vs-table" aria-label="Agency versus We Scale Startups">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th scope="col"></th>
            <th scope="col">Agency</th>
            <th scope="col" class="vs-wss-col">We Scale Startups</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {vsAgency.map((row) => (
            <tr>
              <th scope="row">{row.label}</th>
              <td class="vs-agency-cell">{row.agency}</td>
              <td class="vs-wss-cell">{row.wss}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <ul class="vs-examples" aria-label="Concrete differences in practice">
      <li>
        <strong>Campaigns vs decision rules.</strong> An agency ships the next ads and landing variants. We install the weekly rule for what to scale, stop, or fix — then agencies (if any) execute inside that frame.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Activity reporting vs commercial reporting.</strong> Agencies often report impressions and clicks. We report pipeline, conversion, and payback — tied to a single decision view for the founder and team.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Channel ownership vs system ownership.</strong> Agencies optimize the channel they were hired for. We connect ICP, offer, channels, and cadence so the company owns the growth system, not a vendor roadmap.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p class="vs-footnote">
      If the work needed is "run this channel for me" — go to an agency. If the work needed is "figure out which channel and why, then build the system" — that's us.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .vs-examples {
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.85rem;
    max-width: 72ch;
  }
  .vs-examples li {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--violet);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .vs-examples strong {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
</style>
